other_tests.findings: 100% occlusion of the left anterior descending artery. Left main, left circumflex, and right coronary arteries did not have clinically significant disease.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Successful percutaneous coronary intervention with restoration of normal flow.

other_tests.findings: Ejection fraction of 40%, with hypokinesis of the apex, the middle and distal anterior wall, and the middle and distal anterior septum.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Repeat echocardiogram at 6-month follow-up showed an ejection fraction of 50%.

other_tests.findings: Approximately 70% cellularity, with trilineage hematopoiesis, increased number of megakaryocytes, and reticulin fibrosis.
